Some of the date functions in Hive are:

1.  unix_timestamp(<timestamp string>) -> returns unix time 
2.  from_unixtime(<unix_time>) -> returns corressponding timestamp
3.  TO_DATE(<string timestamp>)
4.  YEAR(<string timestamp>)
5.  MONTH(<string timestamp>)
6.  DAY<string timestamp>)
7.  HOUR(<string timestamp>)
8.  MINUTE(<string timestamp>)
9.  SECOND(<string timestamp>)
10. WEEKOFYEAR(<string timestamp>)
11. DATEDIFF(<string date 1>, <string date 2>)
12. DATE_ADD(<string date>, int days)
13. DATE_SUB(<string date>, int days)


Some of the Mathematical functions in Hive are:

1. ceil(<number>)
2. floor(<number>)
3. round(<number>, <number of digits till which the given number should be rounded>)
4. rand(<seed>)